@startuml
!theme plain

title Salesforce User CRUD System API - Control Flow

actor Client
participant "API Kit Router" as Router
participant "Create User Flow" as CreateFlow
participant "Read User Flow" as ReadFlow
participant "Update User Flow" as UpdateFlow
participant "Delete User Flow" as DeleteFlow
participant "DataWeave Transformer" as DataWeave
participant "Salesforce Connector" as SFConnector
participant "Error Handler" as ErrorHandler
database "Salesforce\n(Custom_User__c)" as Salesforce

== Create User Operation ==
Client -> Router: POST /users\n(User JSON)
activate Router
Router -> Router: Validate Request\n(RAML Spec)
Router -> CreateFlow: Route to Create Flow
activate CreateFlow
CreateFlow -> DataWeave: Transform JSON to\nSalesforce Object
activate DataWeave
DataWeave --> CreateFlow: Transformed Data
deactivate DataWeave
CreateFlow -> SFConnector: Create Custom_User__c
activate SFConnector
SFConnector -> Salesforce: Insert Record
activate Salesforce
alt Success
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: Record Created (ID)
    deactivate Salesforce
    SFConnector --> CreateFlow: Success Response
    deactivate SFConnector
    CreateFlow -> DataWeave: Transform Response to JSON
    activate DataWeave
    DataWeave --> CreateFlow: JSON Response
    deactivate DataWeave
    CreateFlow --> Router: 201 Created
    deactivate CreateFlow
    Router --> Client: User Created Response
else Salesforce Error
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: Error
    SFConnector --> CreateFlow: Exception
    CreateFlow -> ErrorHandler: Handle Exception
    activate ErrorHandler
    ErrorHandler --> CreateFlow: Error Response
    deactivate ErrorHandler
    CreateFlow --> Router: Error Response
    Router --> Client: Error Response
end
deactivate Router

== Read User Operation ==
Client -> Router: GET /users/{id}
activate Router
Router -> Router: Validate Request
Router -> ReadFlow: Route to Read Flow
activate ReadFlow
ReadFlow -> SFConnector: Query Custom_User__c by ID
activate SFConnector
SFConnector -> Salesforce: SELECT Query
activate Salesforce
alt User Found
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: User Record
    deactivate Salesforce
    SFConnector --> ReadFlow: User Data
    deactivate SFConnector
    ReadFlow -> DataWeave: Transform to JSON
    activate DataWeave
    DataWeave --> ReadFlow: JSON Response
    deactivate DataWeave
    ReadFlow --> Router: 200 OK
    deactivate ReadFlow
    Router --> Client: User Data
else User Not Found
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: No Records
    SFConnector --> ReadFlow: Empty Result
    ReadFlow -> ErrorHandler: Handle Not Found
    activate ErrorHandler
    ErrorHandler --> ReadFlow: 404 Response
    deactivate ErrorHandler
    ReadFlow --> Router: 404 Not Found
    Router --> Client: Not Found Error
end
deactivate Router

== Update User Operation ==
Client -> Router: PUT /users/{id}\n(Updated User JSON)
activate Router
Router -> Router: Validate Request\n(RAML Spec)
Router -> UpdateFlow: Route to Update Flow
activate UpdateFlow
UpdateFlow -> DataWeave: Transform JSON to\nSalesforce Object
activate DataWeave
DataWeave --> UpdateFlow: Transformed Data
deactivate DataWeave
UpdateFlow -> SFConnector: Update Custom_User__c
activate SFConnector
SFConnector -> Salesforce: Update Record
activate Salesforce
alt Success
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: Update Success
    deactivate Salesforce
    SFConnector --> UpdateFlow: Success Response
    deactivate SFConnector
    UpdateFlow -> DataWeave: Transform Response to JSON
    activate DataWeave
    DataWeave --> UpdateFlow: JSON Response
    deactivate DataWeave
    UpdateFlow --> Router: 200 OK
    deactivate UpdateFlow
    Router --> Client: Updated User Response
else Update Failed
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: Error
    SFConnector --> UpdateFlow: Exception
    UpdateFlow -> ErrorHandler: Handle Exception
    activate ErrorHandler
    ErrorHandler --> UpdateFlow: Error Response
    deactivate ErrorHandler
    UpdateFlow --> Router: Error Response
    Router --> Client: Error Response
end
deactivate Router

== Delete User Operation ==
Client -> Router: DELETE /users/{id}
activate Router
Router -> Router: Validate Request
Router -> DeleteFlow: Route to Delete Flow
activate DeleteFlow
DeleteFlow -> SFConnector: Delete Custom_User__c by ID
activate SFConnector
SFConnector -> Salesforce: Delete Record
activate Salesforce
alt Success
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: Delete Success
    deactivate Salesforce
    SFConnector --> DeleteFlow: Success Response
    deactivate SFConnector
    DeleteFlow --> Router: 204 No Content
    deactivate DeleteFlow
    Router --> Client: Delete Successful
else Delete Failed
    Salesforce --> SFConnector: Error
    SFConnector --> DeleteFlow: Exception
    DeleteFlow -> ErrorHandler: Handle Exception
    activate ErrorHandler
    ErrorHandler --> DeleteFlow: Error Response
    deactivate ErrorHandler
    DeleteFlow --> Router: Error Response
    Router --> Client: Error Response
end
deactivate Router

@enduml
